	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65373219"><p>Assembly is special-purpose only and (except very early) always has been. But a modern C compiler is not hard to use, code is portable and the binaries are blazingly fast if the coder knows what they are doing. The problem with many other languages is that they needlessly increase the active memory work-set and that decreases chache efficieny. That can cost you a factor of 10x, 100x or even more in performance.</p></div>
	</div>

