			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65373285">		
		on Tuesday May 13, 2025 @11:06AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23691013&amp;cid=65373285">#65373285</a>)
		<small><a href="http://reanjr.org/" title="http://reanjr.org/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65373285"><p>It's amazing how fast software runs when someone actually knows what they're doing.</p><p>I remember having a discussion with coworkers over selecting languages for command line tools.  It's amazing to me that anyone would even think to suggest using Java to write a command line tool. The startup time for Java is atrocious and it's completely inappropriate to use it to write a tool that might get out in a bash loop.</p><p>Simply by thinking for a few moments and choosing something like C or even Bash can make a huge difference in performance with essentially no extra effort (for simple enough tools).</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65373285">
